\title{Type Inference Validation}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{trit}{-1}

\meta{description}{Static type inference and validation for navigation paths}

\subtree{
\title{Type Inference Validation}
\subtree{
\title{Core Concept}
\p{Static type validation that \strong{rejects invalid path compositions before caching}. Every Navigator path must prove type compatibility with its input structure—this skill enforces that proof.}

\p{Works alongside Möbius filtering as a second line of defense: Möbius eliminates topological impossibilities, Type Inference eliminates structural impossibilities.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Why Type Validation?}
\p{Consider this dangerous scenario:}

\pre{\startverb
data_numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
data_dict = Dict("x" => 10, "y" => 20)

# This path makes sense for numbers
nav1 = @late_nav([ALL, pred(iseven)])  # Type ✓: Vector → Numbers → Numbers

# But what if someone mistakenly uses it on the dict?
nav_select(nav1, data_dict, x -> [x])
# => IndexError! (dicts don't support ALL enumeration this way)
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Type Inference Validation prevents this at compile time}, not runtime.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture}
\subtree{
\title{Type System}
\p{Each Navigator carries a \strong{type signature}:}

\pre{\startverb
Navigator{InputType, OutputType, PathSteps}
\stopverb}

\p{Examples:}

\pre{\startverb
nav_vector = Navigator{Vector, Vector, [ALL, pred(f)]}
nav_dict = Navigator{Dict, Vector, [keypath(k), ALL]}
nav_sexp = Navigator{SExpression, Symbol, [sexp_nth(2), SEXP_HEAD]}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Type Refinement Pipeline}
\pre{\startverb
Input Type
    ↓
@late_nav(path_expr) triggers validation
    ↓
Type each step in path:
  [ALL] : Vector{T} → T
  [keypath(k)] : Dict{K,V} → V
  [pred(f)] : T → T (preserves type)
  [INDEX(i)] : Vector{T} → T
  [SEXP_HEAD] : SExpr → Symbol
    ↓
Unify step outputs with next step inputs
    ↓
Final output type computed
    ↓
Cache with type signature
    ↓
Accept or Reject
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Type Incompatibility Detection}
\pre{\startverb
| Step | Input Type | Output Type | Valid? |
|------|-----------|------------|--------|
| `[ALL]` | Vector{T} | T | ✓ |
| `[ALL]` | Dict{K,V} | ⚠️ (ambiguous) | ✗ |
| `[keypath(k)]` | Dict{K,V} | V | ✓ |
| `[keypath(k)]` | Vector{T} | ✗ | ✗ |
| `[pred(f)]` | T | T | ✓ |
| `[INDEX(i)]` | Vector{T} | T | ✓ |
| `[INDEX(i)]` | Dict | ✗ | ✗ |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{API}
\subtree{
\title{Type Inference}
\p{\strong{\code{\startverb infer_type(path_expr, input_type) :: Result{OutputType, Error}\stopverb}} Computes the output type of a path given an input type.}

\pre{\startverb
infer_type([ALL, pred(iseven)], Vector{Int})
# => Result(Int)  # outputs Int values

infer_type([keypath("x"), ALL], Dict{String, Vector{Int}})
# => Result(Int)  # navigates to x, then enumerates integers

infer_type([keypath("x")], Vector{Int})
# => Result(TypeError("Cannot apply keypath to Vector"))
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{\code{\startverb validate_path(navigator::Navigator, input_type) :: Bool\stopverb}} Checks if a Navigator is compatible with a given input type.}

\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(f)])
validate_path(nav, Vector{Int})      # => true
validate_path(nav, Dict{String, Int})  # => false ✗

# Causes @late_nav to reject the Navigator before caching
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Type Signatures}
\p{\strong{\code{\startverb navigator_signature(nav::Navigator) :: TypeSignature\stopverb}} Returns the full type signature of a cached Navigator.}

\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(iseven)])
sig = navigator_signature(nav)

# => TypeSignature(
#     input: Vector{T},
#     output: T,
#     constraints: [iseven(T)],
#     steps: [[ALL], [pred(iseven)]],
#     valid_for: Vector{Int}, Vector{BigInt}, ...
#   )
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Polymorphic Inference}
\p{\strong{\code{\startverb polymorphic_infer(path_expr) :: PolymorphicType\stopverb}} Infers the most general type for a path (before knowing input type).}

\pre{\startverb
polymorphic_infer([ALL, pred(iseven)])
# => ∀T. (T ∈ Enumerable, T ∈ HasEven) → T

# This means: works for ANY type T that:
# - Can be enumerated (Vector, Set, List, etc.)
# - Has an iseven() method defined
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration with Caching}
\p{Cache keys now include type information:}

\pre{\startverb
cache_key = hash((path_expr, inferred_type))

# Different input types → different cache entries
nav_vec = @late_nav([ALL, pred(f)])   # cache for Vector
nav_set = @late_nav([ALL, pred(f)])   # cache for Set (if compatible)
# => Different NavigatorObjects, despite same path!
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Refinement Types}
\p{Supports \strong{refinement types} for predicates:}

\pre{\startverb
# pred(iseven) refines Int → EvenInt
# pred(x -> x > 5) refines Int → IntGt5

nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(x -> x > 5)])
# Type: Vector{Int} → IntGt5
# (output is proven to be > 5)
\stopverb}

\p{Refinement types enable:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Automatic constraint propagation} downstream}
\li{\strong{Proof that outputs satisfy predicates} without re-checking}
\li{\strong{Composition of constraints} with type safety}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Type Mismatch Examples}
\subtree{
\title{❌ INVALID: Wrong container type}
\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([keypath("name"), ALL])
# Type error: keypath returns a string, ALL requires enumerable

# KeyPath{Dict, String} → String
# ALL{String} → ✗ (String not enumerable in that way)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{❌ INVALID: Incompatible predicate}
\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(x -> x > 5)])
# If input is Vector{String}, predicate fails
# Type error: `(String > 5)` is nonsense
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{✓ VALID: Polymorphic path}
\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(identity)])  # identity always works
# Type: ∀T. Vector{T} → T
# Works for ANY vector type
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error Messages}
\p{\strong{Type validation errors are clear}:}

\pre{\startverb
TypeError: Path composition invalid
  Step 1: [ALL]
    Input: Vector{Int}
    Output: Int
    ✓ Type check passed

  Step 2: [keypath("x")]
    Input: Int
    Output: ???
    ✗ TypeError: Cannot apply keypath to Int
       keypath requires Dict or record type
       Got: Int

Suggestion: Remove [keypath("x")] or ensure input is Dict/Struct
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Performance}
\p{All type checking happens at \strong{compile time} (during \code{\startverb @late_nav\stopverb} expansion):}

\pre{\startverb
| Operation | Complexity | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| infer_type | O(\|path\|) | Single pass through steps |
| validate_path | O(1) | Cached signature lookup |
| polymorphic_infer | O(\|path\|) | Compute most general type |
| **Runtime overhead** | O(0) | Zero cost—all checks are static |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Composition with Other Skills}
\p{\strong{Works with Möbius Filtering}:}

\ol{
\li{Möbius filters topological impossibilities}
\li{Type Inference filters structural impossibilities}
\li{Both must pass for path to compile}
}

\p{\strong{Works with Color Envelopes}: Type signatures include color trit information:}

\pre{\startverb
nav = @late_nav([ALL, pred(f)])  # trit = -1 (filtering)
sig = navigator_signature(nav)
# => TypeSignature(..., trit: -1)

# Type system respects color: composition must balance trits AND types
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Enables Constraint Generalization} (next skill): Once types are proven, constraints can be composed and generalized safely.}
}

